<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-10-22T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-10-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">360F.1163 Church of Jesus Christ/9:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Benton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-22T14:00:00+01:00">October 22, 1934—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 22—12:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>54. My number 49, October 11, 4 p.m. Arthur Gaillardth [<hi rend="italic">Gaeth</hi>] informs me case has been
                                satisfactorily settled.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Benton</hi></signed></closer>
